{* get_enhancedA(_x,_cname,_m,_y)                 15-Aug-2008/M.Jeusfeld      *}
{*                                                                            *}
{* get_enhancedA is like get_A but has an additional paramter _cname, which   *}
{* holds the name of the class that defines the attribute with label _m.      *}
{* It basically transforms cname!m to the object identifier cc referenced by  *}
{* this expression. The purpose of get_enhancedA is to speed up certain       *}
{* predicated that were originally of the form A(x,m,y) or A_e(x,m,y).        *}
{* If we know the class that defines the attribute label m, then we can       *}
{* compute the unique identifier cc of cname!m. Then, we can call the         *}
{* efficient Adot instead of the inefficient A predicate.                     *}
{* get_enhancedA will maintain a cache that stores the transformation. Hence, *}
{* the lookup of the attribute id for cname only occurs once per transaction. *}
{* Normally, we would need to refresh the cachedCC table after any update.    *}
{* However, the get_enhancedA function is only used internally by calls of    *}
{* A_e(x,cname,m,y). This predicate is not visible for the user and only      *}
{* used in source modules of the CBserver. Hence, it only ranges over system  *}
{* objects. Those are not supposed to be changed by the user anyway. For this *}
{* reason, we keep the cachedCC table over all transactions and do not assume *}
{* that entries become invalid.                                               *}


#DYNAMIC(cachedCC/3).  {* CC stands for 'concerned class' *}

get_enhancedA(_x,_cname,_ml,_y) :-
  getCC(_cname,_ml,_cc),
  prove_C_Adot(_cc,_x,_,_y).


getCC(_cname,_m,_cc) :-
  cachedCC(_cname,_m,_cc),
  !.

getCC(_cname,_m,_cc) :-
  name2id(_cname,_c),
  retrieve_proposition(P(_cc,_c,_m,_)),
  assert(cachedCC(_cname,_m,_cc)),  
  !.

 
